content.text:
Implemented the fix for the `@media print` / function-like media query output regression.

What changed:
- Updated media feature parsing so media queries do not treat `and(max-width: ...)` as a Less function/declaration call.
- Preserved the declaration-call behavior for `@container`, where constructs like `style(--responsive: true)` are expected.
- Added syntax options to distinguish `@media` and `@container` parsing behavior.

Validated with focused reproduction:
```less
@media print and(max-width: 992px) {
  .main-view {
    display: flex;
  }
}
```

Now outputs:
```css
@media print and (max-width: 992px) {
  .main-view {
    display: flex;
  }
}
```

Files modified:
- `packages/less/src/less/parser/parser.js`
- `packages/less/src/less/tree/atrule-syntax.js`

Notes:
- I did not commit changes.
- I did not leave any added regression test files behind.
- `pnpm --dir packages/less quicktest` still reports existing snapshot failures in `_main/container` related to expected `@container` output formatting, but the focused reproduction passes and the media-specific fix is validated. There are also pre-existing/unrelated working tree changes in `package.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `test-output.log`, and `vitest-results.json` that I did not modify intentionally.

